text: (This article is about Queen consort of Antiochus III of Commagene. For other uses, see Iotapa (disambiguation).) Iotapa (born around 20 BC), a daughter of King Mithridates III of Commagene, reigned as Queen of Commagene after marrying her King brother Antiochus III.

text: Islwyn David John (1933-2009) was Archdeacon of Carmarthen from 1993 until 1999. John was educated at St David's College, Lampeter and ordained in 1959. After curacies in Brynamman and Carmarthen he held incumbencies in Penbryn and Llandysul until his Archdeacon’s appointment.
